= latex =
[[https://launchpad.net/rubber/|rubber]] can be used to preprocess error output
of latex. Then its easy to parse by Vim

More useful plugins:
* [[plugins/vim-addon-actions]]
* [[http://vim-latex.sourceforge.net/|vim-latex]]
* [[http://vim-latex.sourceforge.net/|vim-latex]]
* [[topic/text-snippets-skeletons-templates]]
* [[http://atp-vim.sourceforge.net/features.shtml|AutomaticLaTexPlugin (ATP)]]
* [[http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3109|LaTeX Box]]

There are probably more

== known issues ==
slow syntax highlighting, see 
{{{
 :he g:tex_fast
 :he tex-slow
}}}
Tip by C Campbell from mailinglist

== preview
Okular and Evince reload files (evince needs to get the focus ?).

= alternatives / related =
* Emacs (can preview mathematic formulars)
* Lyx (WYSIWYG for latex like documents)
* Texmacs
* OpenOffice Math / Microsoft Office math have simple math formular editors built in
